refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
boolodbc_execute resourceresult_id arrayparameters_array
Executa um comando preparado com odbc_prepare.

  &reftitle.examples;



    odbc_execute and odbc_prepare example


     In the following code, $success will only be
     &true; if all three parameters to myproc are IN parameters:



<?php
$a = 1;
$b = 2;
$c = 3;
$stmt    = odbc_prepare($conn, 'CALL myproc(?,?,?)');
$success = odbc_execute($stmt, array($a, $b, $c));
?>






   If you need to call a stored procedure using INOUT or OUT parameters,
   the recommended workaround is to use a native extension for your database
   (for example, oci8 for Oracle).
